02/12/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- President Branko Crvenkovski told visiting US Deputy Assistant of State Rosemary DiCarlo on Thursday (1 December) that bilateral ties with Washington are a priority for Skopje.
Crvenkovski's office issued a statement after the meeting, saying the two agreed that solutions to the latest issues in the region must not lead to changes in existing borders and must ensure lasting peace, security and prosperity.
In other news, police announced on Thursday the arrest of seven people in connection with organised trafficking of Albanian migrants to Greece, via Macedonia.
Two other suspects are being sought.
(Makfax, A1 TV, MIA - 01/12/05)
